{
  "bookId": "laozi-wangbi-wiki",
  "num": 16,
  "title": "第十六章",
  "author": "老子",
  "authorId": "Laozi",
  "dynasty": "周",
  "era": "周",
  "genre": "prose",
  "verses": [
    {
      "text": "致虛極，守靜篤。"
    },
    {
      "text": "萬物並作，吾以觀復。"
    },
    {
      "text": "夫物芸芸，各復歸其根。歸根曰靜，是謂復命。復命曰常，"
    },
    {
      "text": "知常曰明。不知常，妄作凶。"
    },
    {
      "text": "知常容，"
    },
    {
      "text": "容乃公，"
    },
    {
      "text": "公乃全，"
    },
    {
      "text": "全乃天，"
    },
    {
      "text": "天乃道，"
    },
    {
      "text": "道乃久，"
    },
    {
      "text": "沒身不殆。"
    }
  ],
  "sections": {},
  "annotations": [],
  "layers": {
    "wangbi": [
      {
        "id": "wangbi-1",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 8
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "言致虛物之極，篤守靜物之真正也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-2",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 1,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 10
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "以虛靜觀其反復。凡有起於虛，動起於靜，故萬物雖並動作，卒復歸於虛靜，是物之極篤也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-3",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 2,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 26
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "歸根則靜，故曰靜。靜則復命，故曰復命也。復命則得性命之常，故曰常也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-4",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 3,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 13
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "常之為物，不偏不彰，無皦昧之狀，溫涼之象，故曰知常曰明也。唯此復，乃能包通萬物，無所不容，失此以往，則邪入乎分，則物離其分，故曰不知常，則妄作凶也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-5",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 4,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 4
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "無所不包通也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-6",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 5,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 4
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "無所不包通，則乃至於蕩然公平也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-7",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 6,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 4
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "蕩然公平，則乃至於無所不周普也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-8",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 7,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 4
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "無所不周普，則乃至於同乎天也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-9",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 8,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 4
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "與天合德，體道大通，則乃至於極虛無也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-10",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 9,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 4
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "窮極虛無，得道之常，則乃至於不窮極也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-11",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 10,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 5
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "無之為物，水火不能害，金石不能殘。用之於心則虎兕無所投其齒角，兵戈無所容其鋒刃，何危殆之有乎。",
        "source": "cham"
      }
    ]
  },
